email: <jeffrey_hanna@health.qld.gov.au>
[The 3 new cases point to local transmission and, as reported in the first
posting, a suspected carrier of _P.vivax_ gametocytes had remained in the
camps through the end of September, which fits with the time it takes the
plasmodia to develop in the mosquito. - Mod.EP]
